text:
="preserve">Jesús Armamento Dosado, C.M. (1 September 1939 – 22 June 2020) was a Filipino Archbishop. He was Archbishop of Ozamiz from 1981 until his retirement in 2016. He was born in Sogod, Cebu. He was ordained priest on 26 May 1966 and became a member of Congregation of the Mission (CM).
Dosado died on 22 June 2020, aged 80.
